To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

records sufficient to show the number of CityKey cards issued per month between August 2021 through September 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of the list of 9-1-1 and/or non-emergency incident call logs between June 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment, for 37607 NE Eagle View Dr Yacolt, WA 98675.

All incident reports from and relating to 37607 NE Eagle View Dr Yacolt, WA 98675 between June 1, 2020, and the date of fulfillment.

I request that you release records for this request on a rolling basis as they become available and in electronic form.

If your agency does not maintain these public records, please let me know who does and include the proper custodian's name and address.

If you choose to deny this request, please provide a written explanation for the denial including a reference to the specific statutory exemption(s) upon which you rely. Also, please provide all segregable portions of otherwise exempt material.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Sincerely,

Albert Serna Jr.

All correspondence, emails, memos, phone memos, texts, letters, or interoffice memos or letters, from County Judge Scott Felton to Sheriff Parnell McNamara, or, underlings of McNamara, Blossman, Eubank, or whomever might have answered or initiated any transmissions between Sheriff and Felton on anything concerning Bitcoin, the handling of the Bitcoin money and victim, or policy on giving money back to victims without court order. Also, any memos, letters, or transmissions from anyone from McLennan County, not limited to Scott Felton, Parnell McNamara or underlings in the SO TO Bitcoin for any reason, including this lawsuit. This is to include memos after phon conversations or any time of file or record of such phone conversations with Bitcoin.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.
